body.description: Finish Jet-Dry Liquid Green 0% dries and prevents spots – for better results than detergent alone! For optimal results, use with your detergents. Experience shiny dishes and spot and film protection (vs. dishwasher detergent alone) with our Finish Jet Dry 0% Dishwasher Rinse Aid. It works with your dishwashing detergent to rinse away stubborn leftover food, spots, and film for sparkling dishes, glasses and utensils. It's easy to use as well! Simply fill your rinse aid dispenser with Finish Jet-Dry 0% Rinse Aid and it will be automatically released in the rinse cycle every time your dishwasher runs.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 24, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Works great, packaging sucks.
reviews.reviewText: The product (solution) itself performs well. Our house has hard water (I could probably make mineral supplements from the deposits left behind after a week of using my small air humidifier) and does not have a water softener system (naughty, naughty). However, our dishes still come out spotless when using this.Along with other reviewers, I have to say that the packaging sucks, specifically the cap. There's no way to pour the liquid into the dishwasher's reservoir with finesse -- you'll have to accept that some of it will slosh out of the bottle onto the door as you tip it over to pour. I got annoyed enough to transfer it to another container to avoid waste. If it weren't for this, I'd have given 5 stars across the board.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars If Your Silpat or Silicone Kitchen Items Taste 'Soapy', Use This Rinse Aid
reviews.reviewText: I switched to this rinse aid after noticing that my silicone utensils and non-stick sheet liners smelled and tasted like detergent after coming out of the dishwasher. I often ended up rewashing these items by hand. We tried unscented dishwasher tabs, but that didn't solve the problem. This unscented rinse aid did the trick. And it seems to be as effective as regular scented rinse aids.I agree with other reviewers that the mechanism is poorly designed and it's easy to be sloppy when filling the reservoir. But that's a universal problem.Will buy again.
